 ('50', 'field', '2', 'en_us', ' the faculty of architecture design and planning is pleased to announce two of its master of architecture students have won the prize for digital innovation in the 2013 australian institute of architects student awards jonathan fernandes and james ye won lee s digital project presented the temporary structure and interior of a moveable theatre space able to be assembled and disassembled in 72 hours the theatre is designed to appear alongside sydney festival s iconic spiegeltent you can pack it away put it in a truck move it somewhere else in a different location and put it up says james it can be placed in different sites says jonathanthe design allows the theatre s sounds and lights to guide audiences movements in and around the space audiences find themselves plunged deep in the immersive environment of the theatre their model s exceptional interactive ceiling was what set them apart the ceiling can adapt depending on the type of theatre performance says jonathan if you need the theatre to be more open the ceiling could raise up if more people need to be accommodated and it could lower to create a more intimate space entrants from three other universities offering architecture in nsw were in the running for the digital innovation prize this achievement for faculty of architecture design and planning students jonathan and james is great exposure says jonathan the faculty of architecture design and planning congratulates james and jonathan on their outstanding success '),
